CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 11, 1956, pg. A15, reads: "Between Dances...at the Frogs' formal in Pittsburgh Room of the Penn-Sheraton Hotel, this quartet got together to exchange views. Note the painting of one of the city's famous bridges in the background.  Left to right: Miss Doris Freeland and her escort, State Senator Harry Cole of Baltimore, Md.; Miss Carmen Young and Lee Washington who flee in from Tacoma, Wash., for the affair."
TitMainTitle: Doris Freeland, Maryland State Senator Harry Cole, Carmen Young, and Lee Washington, posed in Pittsburgh Room, Penn-Sheraton Hotel, for FROGS formal
